      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
        "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "from google.colab import drive\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mount Google Drive\n",
        "drive.mount('/content/drive')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load and preprocess the dataset\n",
        "file_path = '/content/vehicles.csv'  # Update path if needed\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv(file_path)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Basic cleaning (from your code)\n",
        "df = df.dropna(subset=[\"price\", \"year\", \"odometer\"])\n",
        "df = df[df[\"price\"].between(1000, 30000)]\n",
        "df[\"age\"] = 2024 - df[\"year\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Select numerical columns for PCA\n",
        "numeric_cols = ['price', 'odometer', 'age']\n",
        "data = df[numeric_cols]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Standardize the data\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(data)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Perform PCA\n",
        "pca = PCA()\n",
        "pca_data = pca.fit_transform(scaled_data)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Scree plot\n",
        "explained_variance_ratio = pca.explained_variance_ratio_\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
        "plt.plot(range(1, len(explained_variance_ratio) + 1), explained_variance_ratio, marker='o')\n",
        "plt.title('Scree Plot')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Principal Component')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Proportion of Variance Explained')\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.savefig('/content/drive/My Drive/scree_plot.png')  # Save to Google Drive\n",
        "plt.close()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Interpret the first two principal components\n",
        "components = pd.DataFrame(pca.components_, columns=numeric_cols, index=[f'PC{i+1}' for i in range(len(pca.components_))])\n",
        "pc1_loadings = components.loc['PC1'].sort_values(key=abs, ascending=False)\n",
        "pc2_loadings = components.loc['PC2'].sort_values(key=abs, ascending=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"PC1 Loadings (Top contributors):\")\n",
        "print(pc1_loadings)\n",
        "print(\"\\nPC2 Loadings (Top contributors):\")\n",
        "print(pc2_loadings)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Perform K-means clustering on first two principal components\n",
        "kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3, random_state=42)  # Adjust n_clusters as needed\n",
        "clusters = kmeans.fit_predict(pca_data[:, :2])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Visualize clusters\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
        "sns.scatterplot(x=pca_data[:, 0], y=pca_data[:, 1], hue=clusters, palette='viridis')\n",
        "plt.title('K-means Clustering on First Two Principal Components')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Principal Component 1')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Principal Component 2')\n",
        "plt.savefig('/content/drive/My Drive/cluster_plot.png')  # Save to Google Drive\n",
        "plt.close()"
      ]
